
@startuml
' Define classes and their attributes

class School {
  -name: String
}

class Person {
  -firstName: String
  -lastName: String
}

class Teacher extends Person {
  -email: String
}

class Student extends Person {
}

class Principal extends Teacher {
}

class Room {
  -name: String
}

class Classroom extends Room {
  -capacity: Integer
}

class Gym extends Room {
  -size: Integer
}

class ClassGroup {
  -name: String
}

class TeachingAssignment {
  -hours: Integer
}

' Define relationships

School "1" *-- "0..*" Teacher : employs
School "1" --> "1" Principal : hasPrincipal
Teacher "0..3" *-- "1" School : teachesAt
Teacher "0..1" *-- "1" School : isPrincipalOf

School "1" *-- "0..*" Room : hasRoom

ClassGroup "1" *-- "1" Classroom : assignedTo
ClassGroup "1" *-- "10..31" Student : contains
Student "1" *-- "1" ClassGroup : belongsTo
Student "1" *-- "1" School : attends

Teacher "1" *-- "0..*" TeachingAssignment : hasTeachingAssignments
TeachingAssignment "1" *-- "1" School : atSchool

@enduml

---

### Explanation of Key Relationships:

- **`School`**:
  - Has many `Teacher`s.
  - Has one `Principal`, which is a `Teacher`.
  - Has many `Room`s (either `Classroom` or `Gym`).

- **`Teacher`**:
  - Can teach at up to 3 `School`s via `TeachingAssignment`.
  - Can be the principal of exactly one `School`.

- **`Student`**:
  - Belongs to exactly one `ClassGroup`.
  - Attends exactly one `School`.

- **`ClassGroup`**:
  - Assigned to exactly one `Classroom`.
  - Contains between 10 and 31 `Student`s.

- **`Room`**:
  - Can be a `Classroom` (with capacity) or a `Gym` (with size in square meters).

- **`TeachingAssignment`**:
  - Links a `Teacher` to a `School` with a number of hours.

---

